Features of this SuperShop System
Add Product: Allows you to add a new product to the shop by entering its name, price, and quantity.
Display Products: Displays a list of all products with their ID, name, price, and quantity.
Purchase Product: Allows you to purchase a product by entering the product ID and quantity. It will update the product quantity if the purchase is successful.

How to Use
Compile the code using a C compiler (e.g., gcc supershop.c -o supershop).
Run the compiled program (./supershop on Unix-like systems or supershop.exe on Windows).
Follow the menu to add, display, or purchase products.
Feel free to expand this basic system with more features like removing products, updating product details, handling input errors, etc.
